messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 12/23/2002 3:54:43 PM Eastern Standard Time,
GSmith8995@... writes:
> My business name is The SoapSmith. I bet you can figure out what I sell (and
>
> make) and what my last name is. :) Good Luck.

I like "clever"! <g>

I have a friend that breeds Weimaraners (grey bird dogs). Her name is Elena
Smith. Her kennel name is "Silversmith".

I got a puppy from Elena several years ago. The dog's mother's name was
"Page", so we were supposed to use the word "Page" in her registered name. We
chose "Silversmith's Electronic Page" and called her "Beeper".

I had a mobile dog grooming business called "Dogs By The Yard". It was
between that and "At Your Bark and Call". DBTY won out by two votes. <g>

~Kelly
